  "prompt": "What are your weight-loss meals?",
  "response": "Weight-loss meals typically focus on being nutrient-dense, low in calories, and high in fiber and protein to help you feel full and satisfied. Here are some ideas for balanced, weight-loss-friendly meals:\n\n### Breakfast:\n1. **Greek Yogurt Parfait**  \n   - Non-fat Greek yogurt, fresh berries, and a sprinkle of granola or chia seeds.  \n2. **Veggie Omelette**  \n   - Egg whites or a mix of whole eggs, spinach, tomatoes, and mushrooms, served with a slice of whole-grain toast.  \n3. **Overnight Oats**  \n   - Rolled oats, almond milk, chia seeds, and a handful of fruit or nuts for added flavor.\n\n### Lunch:\n1. **Grilled Chicken Salad**  \n   - Mixed greens, grilled chicken breast, cherry tomatoes, cucumbers, and a light vinaigrette.  \n2. **Quinoa Bowl**  \n   - Quinoa, roasted veggies (like zucchini, bell peppers, and broccoli), topped with a lean protein like tofu or grilled chicken.  \n3. **Turkey Wrap**  \n   - Whole-grain tortilla, sliced turkey, lettuce, tomatoes, and mustard or hummus.\n\n### Dinner:\n1. **Baked Salmon with Veggies**  \n   - Baked salmon fillet, steamed asparagus, and a side of quinoa or brown rice.  \n2. **Stir-Fry**  \n   - Shrimp or tofu, mixed stir-fry vegetables (like bell peppers, broccoli, and snap peas), and a light soy or teriyaki sauce.  \n3. **Grilled Chicken with Sweet Potato**  \n   - Grilled chicken breast, roasted sweet potato wedges, and a side of steamed green beans.\n\n### Snacks:\n1. **Apple Slices with Almond Butter**  \n2. **Carrot Sticks with Hummus**  \n3. **Hard-Boiled Eggs**  \n4. **Handful of Nuts** (portion-controlled)\n\n### Tips for Weight-Loss Meals:\n- **Portion Control**: Use smaller plates and watch portion sizes.  \n- **Hydration**: Drink plenty of water throughout the day.  \n- **Limit Processed Foods**: Focus on whole, unprocessed foods.  \n- **Cook at Home**: This allows you to control ingredients and avoid hidden calories.  \n\nRemember, consistency and balance are key to sustainable weight loss! Always consult with a healthcare professional or dietitian for personalized advice.",
